    All Classes and Interfaces

    Class
    Description
    book
    The abstract class `book` defines a model for representing the basic properties and functionalities relevant to books in the system.
    Book
    Represents a Book with various attributes such as id, title, author, description, genre, and a cover image URL.
    BookInfo
    Represents information about a book, including its status and associated book details.
    ControllerClient
    The ControllerClient class extends the ControllerLibrarian class and is responsible for managing client-related menus and operations within the library management system.
    ControllerItemBookInventoryRow
    The ControllerItemBookInventoryRow class handles the behavior and visual representation of a row in the book inventory list for a librarian system.
    ControllerItemBookReservedRow
    The ControllerItemBookReservedRow class manages the behavior and interaction of a UI component representing a reserved book row item in a librarian application.
    ControllerItemBookRow
    ControllerItemBookRow is a controller class designed to manage the behavior and interactions of individual book items represented as rows in the user interface.
    ControllerItemClientRow
    The ControllerItemClientRow class represents a JavaFX controller for managing a client row in the user interface.
    ControllerLibrarian
    The ControllerLibrarian class is responsible for managing the librarian's GUI functionality, including navigating between panes, displaying client information, handling button interactions, and managing the main Controller.
    ControllerLibrarian
    The ControllerLibrarian class is responsible for managing the user interface and backend logic of a library management system for a librarian role.
    ControllerLibrarian.popup_info_case
     
    ControllerMain
    This class serves as the main controller for managing the application's user interface and functionality.
    ControllerUser
     
    DatabaseConnection
    Represents a utility class for handling database connections and operations.
    DBComands
    The DBComands class provides a collection of methods for interacting with a database.
    ImReading
    The ImReading class is responsible for managing and displaying a list of books currently associated with a user.
    LibrarianMain
    The LibrarianMain class extends the JavaFX Application class to create and manage a graphical user interface for a library application.
    MainApp
    The MainApp class extends the JavaFX Application class to serve as the main entry point for launching a graphical user interface application.
    MyReads
    The MyReads class represents a user's collection of books in a reading list.
    myReadsScroll
    The myReadsScroll class is a custom JavaFX ScrollPane designed to display a grid of book covers with interactive functionality for selection and actions such as deletion or click-handling.
    PaneCarte
    PaneCarte is a custom UI component that displays information about a book in a visually structured horizontal layout.
    Review
    Represents a review entry associated with a user and a book.
    ReviewScroll
    The ReviewScroll class is a custom extension of the ScrollPane that acts as a container for displaying user reviews associated with a specific book.
    ScrollPanel
    Represents a custom scrollable panel designed for displaying a grid of book covers.
    SearchResultsScroll
    Represents a custom scroll pane for displaying a list of books as a scrollable grid.
    Star
    Represents a visual star UI component that extends the Button class.
